<p>I'm happy to talk about open source phone software, and I think there's a reasonable debate to be had there. But this post isn't an example of Google "letting you use the hardware however you please."  It's an example of circumventing restrictions, at your own risk, to use the hardware in a different way -- which many people have done and continue to do with their iPhones as well.</p>
